        "title": "Promotion",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "Open Gate Recording",
        "description": "Unleash your vision with full-sensor 7K 30p RAW Open Gate (3:2 aspect). Capture every pixel across the entire sensor — perfect for flexible reframing in both horizontal and vertical formats. Whether you’re crafting cinematic widescreen films or social-ready vertical edits, every angle starts with 7K clarity."
      },
      {
        "title": "7K 60p RAW",
        "description": "Capture 7K 60p RAW (Light) internally using 17:9 of the full-frame sensor. Every pixel delivers extraordinary detail and natural depth with complete 12-bit tonal integrity."
      },
      {
        "title": "Waveform",
        "description": "Provides a real-time display of the input signal's brightness levels (line display/RGB parade), letting you keep an eye on them as you shoot."
      },
      {
        "title": "Recording Indicators",
        "description": "The tally lamp and red frame indicator on the LCD provide clear visual confirmation when recording is active—enabling remote status checks and helping you avoid costly recording mistakes."
      },
      {
        "title": "Proxy or Sub Recording",
        "description": "Shoot 7K RAW or 4K DCI to CFexpress while simultaneously recording lightweight 2K DCI proxy or 4K sub files to SD. Matching timecode and file names keep everything perfectly synced for seamless post-production workflows. Apply Look Files to your proxies so editors see your creative intent immediately—while the main RAW file retains complete grading flexibility for finishing."
      },
      {
        "title": "14-bit\nRAW",
        "description": "Maximum dynamic range, colour depth, and image data—total creative control in post."
      },
      {
        "title": "Enhanced Design & Operability",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "Dual Card Slots",
        "description": "The EOS R6 Mark III doubles your storage capacity with intelligent dual card slots: one SD card slot (SD/SDHC/SDXC, UHS-II compatible) and one CFexpress Type B slot. This configuration enables versatile recording workflows—separate video and photo storage, simultaneous main and proxy video recording, or real-time backup recording across both cards for critical shoots where data security is paramount."
      },
      {
        "title": "Strong & Durable",
        "description": "The EOS R6 Mark III utilises premium magnesium alloy throughout its body and exterior panels, delivering exceptional structural rigidity while maintaining a lightweight profile."
      },
      {
        "title": "Connectivity",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "image.canon Cloud",
        "description": "The EOS R6 Mark III connects seamlessly to image.canon, Canon's free cloud platform built for backup and collaboration. Original files upload automatically and are sorted intelligently by subject, face, and sharpness—saving hours of post-shoot organisation."
      },
